I think they are the only 2 who get the baton aside from Hoshi.

I just always feel there is some symbolism there that I'm missing haha.

author: @kimmmikk
text:
for anyone wanting to learn this dance(SOLO) i recommend on following these members:

Jun from start to mingyu's part 
S.coups for his own part until Joshua's part
DK for vernon's part

Prechorus -
Jun in Woozi's part (He makes it look easy yet complex looking, if you get what i mean)
Mingyu for DK's part (he does all the movements on that part)

Chorus-
Mingyu for the chorus 
Jun or Dk for HOshi's part (cause if you wanna do Dino's part go for Jun but if not go for DK)
Jun for Dino's part until to the end

Jun again for wonwoo's part
for jun's and hoshi's part you can do one but not both cause it'll look messy in my opinion

Pre-Chorus#2-
For Seungkwan's part i recommend to follow Jun cause if you saw in the choreo Hoshi moves right to the side so if you picked Hoshi in the previous one and continue to follow you'll have to pause cause if you're doing this SOLO then it'll look abit awkward imo
 
Chorus #2-
This one is complicated so if you want continuously dance then follow Wonwoo until Jeonghan part on the chorus but if you want a bit of pause then follow Mingyu 
Repeat the last move in Jeonghan's part (like the dancers in the back did)  

Bridge?-
For vernon's to The8's iconic part i also recommend to follow The8 and Vernon for that 
follow Seungkwan for Dino and Scoup's part and Also follow Seungkwan if you wanna do the dance break (not the feet)
Also a bit of tip i recommend to search on youtube for the foot dancebreak cause i think if you wanna learn that foorwork here then goodluck and wow ^o^

Last Chorus-
For this follow Dino then follow Jun when they all spread out 
For wonwoo's part either follow Wonwoo or Jun ^^

NOTE:
Most of this Jun because despite the way he dances is something you could easyly follow so yeah (and im a Jun bias too so ^^)
Anyways if you did follow this guide then pls let me know if it worked well for you and if you have any tips on it awell ^^
- Thank you and have a best day!!

author: @LadyDi016
text:
I always love to see the choreography they film because I can see every detail and how they wanted it to look to the audience. It's amazing how you can see the little details.
The way Hoshi holds the baton throughout the dance and passes it to the boys is impeccable. The dancers' parts stand out more and are better visualized and appreciated. The part of Scoup and Jeonghan directing the dancers and how they join the choreo in the beats is amazing. Of course, the synchronization is always flawless. I always end up watching the video a thousand times, first watching it in general, then watching it again to see the details I didn't see before. Then I focus on each of the guys and then also when you do group scenes. And of course I never miss Hoshi's haranguing, I love him.

text: Been trying to figure out what makes Wonwoo's dance during the chorus part so satisfying to watch (aside from the quick shift of facial expressions ofc), and noticed he does this slight "recoil" with his head when he shifts his head left and right(more noticeable at 2:13). The members usually swivel(?) their head smoothly left and right, whereas Wonwoo's looks more constricted and maybe even mechanical like(?), which i find as such a great subtle detail to the choreo. He kinda looks like a puppet tied up, passively dancing along to its "master" fingers and commands, which lowkey fits the concept of maestro~

author: @chai_kerry
text:
Guys, don't you realize that Seventeen did sampled their own choreographies from previous songs? Here's the details that I find :

0:46 - The raising hand move from 'HOT'
0:57 - The domino effect similar to The8's part in 'Thanks'
1:49 - hand gesture of drinking poison from 'Fear'
2:26 - well, it might be debatable but it kinda reminds me of Mingyu's part in 'Super', after the "darumdarimda" part

Maybe you guys will find anything more interesting in their choreography besides synchronization, sharpness, precise, etc. I think they're really not joking about bringing all the previous albums in this comeback. 

And yes, Seventeen is so on fire in this comeback! Let's support them as best as we can!!!

author: @aggid9132
text: I just realized something about Seventeen and I absolute adore how they (and the staff) take care of each member. I remember Minghao were absent for most of Super's choreography until his part and they make his part a huge thing by incorporating his lack of presence as something like a final boss thing; of course we know this is because Minghao is still recovering. And in Maestro, they give S.Coups and Jeonghan more rest by letting them absent for almost half a song, but when they're back into the choreography, they make their role essential; in this case by leading the background dancer like a maestro. I know this is just a small thing, but I really love how they take care of each other and accomodating towards each other needs.
